function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` higher-order function from Julia's standard library. The anonymous function `word -> isuppercase(word[1])` checks if the first character of each word is uppercase using the `isuppercase` function. The `filter` function creates a new collection containing only the elements of `words` that satisfy this condition.
